data.enText: a part of the body that has a particular purpose, such as the heart or the brain; part of a plant with a particular purpose
the sense organs (= the eyes, ears, nose, etc.)
a large musical instrument with keys like a piano. Sounds are produced by air forced through pipes.

data.chText: 她在教堂负责弹奏管风琴。
data.enText: She plays the organ in church.
a musical instrument similar to a pipe organ , but without pipes
an official organization that is part of a larger organization and has a special purpose

data.chText: 机关报刊；（某团体的）宣传工具
data.enText: a newspaper or magazine that gives information about a particular group or organization; a means of communicating the views of a particular group

data.chText: 《人民日报》是中国共产党的官方报纸。
data.enText: The People's Daily is the official organ of the Chinese Communist Party.

ex.enText: The brain is the organ of thought.

ex.chText: 鳃是鱼类用来呼吸的器官。
ex.enText: Gills are the organ through which fish breathe.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，可指人体或动植物的器官。
医学术语，通常指人体的器官，一般用单数。

tr: (music) an electronic simulation of a pipe organ
a free-reed instrument in which air is forced through the reeds by bellows
wind instrument whose sound is produced by means of pipes arranged in sets supplied with air from a bellows and controlled from a large complex musical keyboard
a fully differentiated structural and functional unit in an animal that is specialized for some particular function
a periodical that is published by a special interest group
example: the organ of the communist party

tr: a government agency or instrument devoted to the performance of some specific function
example: The Census Bureau is an organ of the Commerce Department

value.def: An organ is a part of your body that has a particular purpose or function, for example your heart or lungs.

example.ex: ...damage to the muscles and internal organs.

value.def: An organ is a large musical instrument with pipes of different lengths through which air is forced. It has keys and pedals rather like a piano.
You refer to a newspaper or organization as the organ of the government or another group when it is used by them as a means of giving information or getting things done.

example.ex: The Security Service is an important organ of the State...
example.tran: 军情五处是国家的重要机构。

example.ex: The most powerful organ of government in Scotland is the Scottish Office.
example.tran: 苏格兰职权最大的政府部门是苏格兰事务部。

trans: 手摇风琴(街头卖艺常用)
(教堂或音乐厅内的)风琴楼厢
